ResourceTokenRegistry_mint
├── when caller is not an authorized minter
│   └── it should revert with NotAuthorizedMinter
└── when caller is an authorized minter
    ├── given recipient already holds this token ID
    │   └── it should revert with BalanceExceedsMax
    └── given recipient does not hold this token ID
        ├── given token ID does not exist yet
        │   ├── it should set the creator to msg.sender
        │   ├── it should store the metadata
        │   ├── it should set the balance to 1
        │   ├── it should emit TokenCreated
        │   └── it should emit Transfer
        └── given token ID already exists
            ├── it should not change the creator
            ├── it should not change the metadata
            ├── it should set the balance to 1
            └── it should emit Transfer

ResourceTokenRegistry_burn
├── when caller is not the token creator
│   └── it should revert with NotTokenCreator
└── when caller is the token creator
    ├── given holder balance is 0
    │   └── it should revert with InsufficientBalance
    └── given holder balance is 1
        ├── it should set the balance to 0
        └── it should emit Transfer

ResourceTokenRegistry_transfer
├── when caller is not the token creator
│   └── it should revert with NotTokenCreator
└── when caller is the token creator
    ├── given receiver already holds this token ID
    │   └── it should revert with BalanceExceedsMax
    └── given receiver does not hold this token ID
        ├── it should set sender balance to 0
        ├── it should set receiver balance to 1
        └── it should emit Transfer

ResourceTokenRegistry_transferFrom
├── when caller is not the token creator
│   └── it should revert with NotTokenCreator
└── when caller is the token creator
    ├── given receiver already holds this token ID
    │   └── it should revert with BalanceExceedsMax
    └── given receiver does not hold this token ID
        ├── it should set sender balance to 0
        ├── it should set receiver balance to 1
        └── it should emit Transfer

ResourceTokenRegistry_approve
└── it should revert with ApprovalsDisabled

ResourceTokenRegistry_setOperator
└── it should revert with ApprovalsDisabled

ResourceTokenRegistry_registerMinter
├── when caller is not the owner
│   └── it should revert with NotOwner
└── when caller is the owner
    ├── it should set isMinter to true
    └── it should emit MinterRegistered

ResourceTokenRegistry_tokenMetadata
├── given token ID does not exist
│   └── it should return empty bytes
└── given token ID exists
    └── it should return the metadata set on first mint

ResourceTokenRegistry_creator
├── given token ID does not exist
│   └── it should return address(0)
└── given token ID exists
    └── it should return the first minter address

ResourceTokenRegistry_tokenType
├── given token ID has 0x01 prefix
│   └── it should return 0x01
├── given token ID has 0x02 prefix
│   └── it should return 0x02
└── given token ID has 0x03 prefix
    └── it should return 0x03

ResourceTokenRegistry_isPermission
├── given token ID has 0x01 prefix
│   └── it should return true
└── given token ID does not have 0x01 prefix
    └── it should return false

ResourceTokenRegistry_isResponsibility
├── given token ID has 0x02 prefix
│   └── it should return true
└── given token ID does not have 0x02 prefix
    └── it should return false

ResourceTokenRegistry_isDirective
├── given token ID has 0x03 prefix
│   └── it should return true
└── given token ID does not have 0x03 prefix
    └── it should return false
